For each asset record in 'data':
1. Take the asset_id field value.
2. Strip all leading alphabetic prefix characters (e.g. SLGT, CB, TX, PM) and any leading zeros to produce a bare_id (SLGT00302876 → 302876, CB00045 → 45, TX0001234 → 1234).
3. Search the SITE PLAN TEXT for the bare_id as a text token or label.
4. If found: examine the context immediately surrounding the bare_id to infer which drawing symbol is associated with it. Match that context to the best-fitting entry in reference_data by comparing symbol descriptions and labels. Set symbol_description and label from the matched legend entry. Set match_status to 'found'.
